Old Fashioned Doughnuts
  -- Vallery Lomas

1/2 c (100g) granulated sugar
2 tbsp (28g) unsalted butter, room temperature
2 large egg yolks
2 1/2 c (250g) cake flour + extra as needed
1 1/2 tsp baking powder
1 tsp kosher salt
2/3 c (160g) sour cream
Vegetable oil, for the bowl

Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add yolks, one at a time, and mix until fully incorporated, scraping down the bowl as needed. Combine the dry ingredients in a bowl. Add dry ingredients and sour cream, alternating and mixing between each addition. Finish by hand, ensuring all ingredients are incorporated, but do not overmix. Chill dough for 1 hr to overnight. Flour 2 sheets of parchment and place dough between, rolling out to 1/2-3/4" thick. Punch out doughnuts and holes, do not twist, just push straight down. Place on a baking sheet lined with parchment, dusted with flour. Bring oil to 325F, fry doughnuts in batches, turning once side is gbd. Remove done ones to a paper towel lined rack to drain excess oil off. Glaze while hot/warm.



